Today we complete your loop mastery with 2 powerful concepts:

👉 do-while loop
👉 break & continue (control flow — VERY IMPORTANT for interviews)

🧠 Concept 1: do-while Loop (Execute First, Check Later)
✅ What it is

👉 A loop that runs at least once, even if condition is false

do {
    // code
} while (condition);
💡 Real-World Analogy

👉 Think:

You try food once 🍜, then decide if you want more

First → eat
Then → decide
⚙️ Why it works (Important 🔥)

👉 Difference from while:

while	do-while
Check first	Execute first
May not run	Runs at least once
🔥 Key Insight
int i = 10;

do {
    printf("%d", i);
} while (i < 5);

👉 Output:

10

🔥 Even though condition is false → runs once

💻 Example
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int i = 1;

    do {
        printf("%d ", i);
        i++;
    } while (i <= 5);

    return 0;
}
🔗 Connection to what you know
Same in Java/C++
Rarely used in Python (no direct equivalent)
🧠 Memory Trick

👉 Remember:

“do-while = first do, then check”

🧠 Concept 2: break & continue (Control the Loop)
✅ What it is

👉 These are control statements used inside loops

🔴 break → STOP the loop completely
💡 Analogy

👉 You are watching a boring movie 🎬
→ You leave immediately

💻 Example
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
        if (i == 5) {
            break;
        }
        printf("%d ", i);
    }
    return 0;
}

👉 Output:

1 2 3 4
🟡 continue → SKIP current iteration
💡 Analogy

👉 Teacher calls roll number

If absent → skip
Continue with next student
💻 Example
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
        if (i == 3) {
            continue;
        }
        printf("%d ", i);
    }
    return 0;
}

👉 Output:

1 2 4 5
⚙️ Why it works (Important 🔥)

👉 break → exits loop immediately
👉 continue → skips rest of loop body and jumps to next iteration

🔥 Internal Flow Difference
Statement	Effect
break	exit loop
continue	skip iteration
🔗 Connection to what you know
Same in Java/C++
Python also has both
🧠 Memory Trick

👉 Remember:

“break = exit, continue = skip”

